Privacy Policy for using the Boulder Challenge App
As of: January 2021
The original version was written in German. In case of discrepancies always the original version is preferred and valid.
1. Privacy at a glance
General notes
The following notes give a simple overview of what happens to your personal information when you use the Boulder Challenge App. Personal information is any data that personally identifies you.
Who is responsible for data collection?
The data processing of the Boulder Challenge App is carried out by the service operator. Its contact details can be found in the imprint.
How do we collect your information?
On one hand, your data is collected by communicating it to us. This may be e.g. data you enter when registering or when you upload a picture of a boulder.
Other data will be collected automatically when using the Boulder Challenge App through our IT systems. These are above all technical data (for example IP address or time of the service call). The collection of this data is automatic, as soon as you use the Boulder Challenge App.
What do we use your data for?
Part of the data is collected to ensure a flawless delivery of the Boulder Challenge App. Other data can be used to analyze your user behavior.
What rights do you have regarding your data?
You have the right at any time free of charge to obtain information about the origin, recipient and purpose of your personal data stored. You also have a right to request the correction, blocking or deletion of this data. You can contact us at any time at the address given in the imprint.
Analytics tools and third-party tools
The use of the Boulder Challenge App services can be statistically evaluated. This is usually done anonymously. The usage behavior can not be traced back to you. Detailed information can be found in the following privacy policy.
2. General information and mandatory information
Privacy
The operators of the Boulder Challenge App take the protection of your personal data very seriously. We treat your personal data confidentially and in accordance with the statutory data protection regulations and this privacy policy.
If you use the Boulder Challenge App, various personal information will be collected. Personal information is information that personally identifies you. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect and what we use it for. It also explains how and for what purpose this happens.
Please note that data transmission over the internet (for example, in the communication between client and server) may have security vulnerabilities. A complete protection of the data from access by third parties is not possible.
Note to the responsible body
The responsible data processing unit of the Boulder Challenge App is:
Christian Fenzl
